680), this monograph rethinks some crucial issues in the reading of political history in the seventeenth century. Most importantly, it invites new reflections on the theory of patriarchalism and gives novel insights into the place of patriotism in the development of English political discourse and identity.Thanks to its originality in both approach and content, this volume will be of interest to historians of early modern England as well as scholars of political thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMonarchyzGreat BritainxHistoryy17th century. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 17th Century.2bisacsh  aContext.  aFilmer.  aPatriarchalism.  aPatriotism.  aPolitical thought.  aStuart era.1 aCuttica, Cesare, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978178499227940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784992279423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784992279/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles